Klotz observes that the Scholiast made a correct remark on this: “ Popularis magis quam pressa et gravis haec sententia vide- tur3 sed facit ad aures vulgi, ut quum parentes procreaverint hominem, ipsi pro- vexisse et quodammodo gradibus honorum conroborasse videantur senatoriam dignita- tem.'' Klotz observes that we might add that Cicero made almost the whole of this introduction simply for the people; a very probable conjecture. Whom should he have made it for except those to whom it was addressed? And we must, he says, judge of it after this standard, if we would not be unjust towards our orator.
